childNodes.textContent: Easily troubleshoot issues that would otherwise go unnoticed, like confusing navigation, hidden CTAs, and bugs.

Watch users as they engage with new features and identify areas for optimization to add to your roadmap.
Use Sprig Replays to capture the most valuable user moments
Record specific clips of your users’ web and mobile experience based on their unique attributes and in-product actions.
Collect users’ session interactions alongside their Survey feedback to see exactly what influenced their sentiment.
Let Sprig review and organize Replay clips into groups to uncover hidden patterns in your users’ product behavior.
Get an inside look into your product experience
Easily install Sprig into your app

attributes.alt: Easily install Sprig into your app

childNodes.textContent: Customize your Sprig privacy settings to blur sensitive user information in your Replays, including form content, images, and password fields.
Leverage your own product data to specify the sessions you want to record and for how long. Capture quick clips up to 5 minutes before or after your Replay triggers.
Plus, add a Replay into a Survey
Add Replays into your in-product Surveys, so you can collect your users’ sessions and sentiment together and understand why users do what they do.
Explore AI-generated Replay clip categories to see patterns and trends in your users’ behavior. Plus, only view the most relevant clips by filtering on user attributes and survey responses.
Sprig Replays are packed with industry-leading features
Trigger your Replays based on specific user actions and characteristics your product already tracks.
Watch your users’ product interactions, including their cursor activity, clicks, page scrolls, and mouseovers.
Automatically organize your Replay clips into groups based on specific actions your users take in your product.
Blur form content, images, password fields, and/or specific CSS selectors in your users’ screen recordings.
Filter Replay clips by time period and user attributes to see how behavior changes over time and across cohorts.
Review Replay clips efficiently with the ability to adjust your video speed and skip past periods of user inactivity.

If you’ve ever wanted to see exactly how customers use your product, a session replay lets you see just that. This feature captures clips of users interacting with your product. See everything from mouse clicks and keystrokes to page scrolls and cursor activity. Session replay gives you a clear picture of user journey pain points, from bugs to unclear calls to action. Use session replay to improve conversion rates as you see exactly where users are dropping off.

software includes an advanced feature that triggers a “replay” when users conduct specific actions on your site. This way, you can get even more detailed insights into the ways users navigate your product. With Sprig Replays, you can view users' session interactions alongside their survey responses to get a complete picture of their experience. That’s more actionable data to help you further enhance your product.

Session replays work by capturing user interactions with your product in real-time. As users navigate through your website or web application, the product records their actions. This data is then processed and stored as clips that you can view and analyze.
What is session replay used for?

Session replay software is especially powerful in helping you understand and analyze user interactions with your product. You can use these insights to easily identify friction points and make decisions about ways to improve your platform's overall usability.
Sprig is extremely user friendly. Their Replays tool has uncovered insights that we wouldn't have known before.
See the Sprig platform for yourself and start collecting game-changing insights today.
